cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DC, cs.NE, cs.CV. 

The paper proposes a distributed deep learning model for reinforcement learning, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The use of deep Q-networks and convolutional neural networks indicates that it could be in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The adaptation of the DistBelief software framework for efficient training of reinforcement learning agents suggests that it could also belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The use of raw pixels as input and the mention of achieving success on a simple game suggests that it could also be in the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
